  "text": "A note on the inversion. To speed up the relatively costly inversion we can batch several inversions and use Montgomery's trick [CITATION_1] : m batched inversions can be computed with 3(m − 1) multiplications and one inversion. For example, m = 64 batched elliptic curve additions take 2 · 64 + 3 · (64 − 1) = 317 multiplications, 64 squarings and 1 inversion. This corresponds to 4.953 multiplications, 1 squaring and 0.016 inversions for a single elliptic-curve addition.",
